                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3768: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Deputy Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Biddle</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tours</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-14T07:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 14, 1940—7 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 14—3:54 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>10. I was telephoned at 5:30 this morning that French Government is proceeding to
                    Bordeaux region today. I am now en route to see Reynaud some 70 kilometers
                    distant and will telegraph as soon as possible thereafter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Biddle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
